cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.COMM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on the use of 5G NR technology for air-to-ground communication systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the feasibility of using 5G NR technology for air-to-ground communication systems and evaluates its performance in different frequency bands. This involves the use of information theory concepts and techniques. 

3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - In-flight connectivity requires high data rates to support multimedia applications such as video streaming. The paper discusses how 5G NR technology can provide significantly improved data rates for in-flight connectivity, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 

4. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper discusses the challenges associated with 5G NR-based air-to-ground communication systems and proposes enhancements to counteract these challenges. This falls under the domain of communications and networking. 

5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of 5G NR technology for air-to-ground communication systems, which involves the design and control of complex systems. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
